description: Application under S73 of the Town and Country Planning Act for a minor material amendment to Planning Permission PA/11/0642 dated 22nd March 2012 by way of varying condition 2 (NMA PA/12/3206) and condition 25 (noise testing) and conditions 34 (use of the commercial and community units), 35 (no amalgamation commercial and community units) and 48 (energy) to allow the following        Adjustment to pedestrian route through piazza to Chamber Street;         Inclusion of smoke extract roof plant and details of the boiler flue;         Adjustment to north elevation of blocks B, C and D and widening of the link blocks;         Addition of 3m catch tray to northern façade and eastern elevation;         Adjustment to the internal cores and entrance from piazza to blocks B, C and D;         Adjustment to residential layouts, reducing the number of units in blocks BCD from 275 to 263;         Adjustment to balcony and window details;         Inclusion of comfort cooling;         Amendment to energy strategy and variation of provision of photovoltaic cells;         Adjustments to cycle stores and car parking;         Adjustment to layouts of the arches below and to the rear of blocks A, B, C and D;         Adjustment to refuse storage;         Amendments to provision of shared amenity and play space within blocks B, C and D;         Adjustment to ground and mezzanine to the eastern façade of block A; and,         Adjustment to basement layout.  These minor material amendments are to permission (PA/11/00642) which consented a mixed-use development comprising the erection of two buildings of between 3 and 15 storeys, providing 354 residential units (Use Class C3), a 236 room hotel together with 33 serviced apartments (Use Class C1), flexible retail/financial services/restaurant/cafe/drinking establishment/health clinic/business space (1172sqm) (Use Classes A1, A2, A3, A4, D1 and B1), restaurant, bar, gallery, leisure (731sqm) (Use Class A3/A4/D1/D2), community uses including sports and training facilities, neighbourhood police base and office space within the railway arches (1,014sq.m) (Use Class D1/D2/B1), creation of new public open space, alterations to the existing highway, and new pedestrian link, together with associated works including landscaping, providing of parking, servicing and plant area.
